Description: Fly Guys, owned by iSkyView LLC is a company comprised of federally compliant drone pilots, professional photographers, computer............
Full Description: Fly Guys, owned by iSkyView LLC is a company comprised of federally compliant drone pilots, professional photographers, computer programmers, digital media and marketing automation experts, and post production film and photograph editing specialists with a couple of programmers tossed in the mix.  The company has a growing fleet of 8 drones and many different camera and data sensing attachments to handle any job. This means that any job can be delivered, from raw aerial footage delivered on a CD or USB (thumb) drive, to a finished promotional product complete with a custom soundtrack, and anything in between.  Fly Guys is fundamentally a family owned and operated company. The founding brothers, Nick and Tim Handley, both pilots that: Have a love for innovation, a passion for delivering stunning value in an elegant and efficient manner, and complementary production skills with one being the artist and the other being the technician; We will let you figure out which is which!  Fly Guys is more than a company, it is a movement. There is so much value to be delivered by implementing drone technology, and so few qualified compliant people to deliver it. We consider it in our professional ethos to help clients realize this value. Though admittedly, that is unlikely as in addition to the above core competencies, Fly Guys brings many ancillary skill sets to the table because they are: Musicians, a sound and audio production engineer (with a studio), a programmer and web developer, a 5 time inductee into the INC 500, a wedding DJ, a professional photographer and videographer, a firefighter, a plus handicap golfer, a construction engineer, maybe even a Russian and the list goes on.  While the drone commercial space is very new so little commercial experience can legally be claimed, Fly Guys' pilots have ample flight time, flying and recording many events, golf courses and many other venues for hobby and prototype purposes. Being pilots, Fly Guys' dedication to safety trumps all other concerns. So rigorous methodology is employed to assure safety for all those in proximity of the drone operations as well as the airworthiness of the drones.

Description: The 3rd Sensation phone app uses the latest internet techniques and phone technology to add vibration to your videos.
Full Description: The 3rd Sensation phone app uses the latest internet techniques and phone technology to add vibration to your videos. A typical phone video affects the capacity of the human senses in two ways, the sense of sight and sense of hearing. Now you can add a third sensation to your video, the sense of touch! The 3rd Sensation suite is comprised of three main components formatted on the Apple platform. The first is the “3rd Sensation Viewer” phone app, which is used to watch and feel your video on the iPhone. We will offer a Droid Platform “3rd Sensation Viewer” app at a later date. The second is the “3rd Sensation Developer”, which is a Mac PC app based on the Lion OS. The 3rd Sensation Developer is used to define the timing points for the vibration events during your video so you can achieve the most dramatic effect of sight, sound and the third sensation of feeling the video action. Later this summer we will offer a Microsoft PC OS version for the“3rd Sensation Developer”. The third component of the 3rd Sensation suite is the “3rd Sensation Host Driver”. This web site component integrates the phone and internet to achieve a high impact on the senses.    Third Sensation © is owned by McCray Media Works, LLC, a Virginia limited liability company headquartered in Richmond, Virginia. The brainchild of founders, Keith and Duane McCray, the company was formed in June 2012. The company is run by its founders and led by an executive committee of techies, marketing professionals, designers, lawyers, investors relations professionals and accountants.    McCray Media Works, LLC received approval for its Third Sensation iPhone App in 2012 and has uploaded its newest version 1.1 which is available for purchase.    The company is developing this proprietary technology to be delivered on a variety of platforms and servers.

Full Description: HourVille is a marketplace where people buy and sell virtually anything that can be priced by the hour — services, rentals, places, classes. Local Search — tag-based local search within a zip code radius for buyers to find local providers of services, rentals, places, and classes in target categories such as lessons, tutoring, babysitting, photography, party entertainment and equipment, massage therapy, dance halls and other venues, and art, computer, and other classes. Multimedia Profiles — Sellers post descriptions, pictures, video, documents, references and testimonials. Online Schedule Management — Sellers create a schedule for their services and post their availability to their profiles via an interactive calendar. Sellers can sync their schedules with other calendar applications via an iCalendar export. Buyers book and buy time directly through the sellers' interactive calendars at HourVille.com.  Ratings and Reviews — Buyers leave feedback for sellers after services have been delivered. Sellers build a community reputation and buyers make informed purchasing decisions based on seller reputation.  Marketing and Promotional Tools — Third-party web site support and integration is available through tools such as a widgets (including Facebook), and links and buttons that sellers embed in Craigslist and other online classifieds postings and personal and company web sites. The links, buttons, and widgets pull buyers back to sellers' HourVille profiles and interactive calendars. Pricing, Payment and Auctions — Sellers set prices for hourly service time slots via fixed price or auctions. Buyers buy and pay for services through PayPal and Google Checkout integration.
